messages.text: I did it!
Where were u?! I thought u died!!
I just had a long meet with investigative reporter Matt Anthony.
He's gonna run the story.
r u sure u know what ur doing?
This way the truth will come out.
Aren't you worried about revealing something that you don't expect?
Something that could hurt you more?
I'm pretty numb already these past weeks.
Don't think I can get hurt worse.
And you? Don't you want to see your dad home, not in jail?
Of course! But why are YOU so determined to see YOUR dad in jail?
It's for justice. The same as what you've been fighting for.
Like when you organized a protest against police brutality,
and lobbied for gun control.
It seems that for you it's so personal.
What did he do to you?
He was never around. And when he was, it wasn't pretty.
Eventually I got taller and faster.
After a while he couldn't catch me to hit me.
But when he started hitting my mom --
well, she left and I stayed. I didn't want to leave you behind.
When my folks fight they just turn quiet. Sometimes for weeks.
My mom is the one who keeps us together.
"Don't give up the ship" is what she always says.
Even now?
Especially now.
If this story gets out the way I think it will
your family can stay together
not be split apart.
I hope u know what ur doing?
Me too.
the next day
Hey, where's the story?
Hi Tom. Thanks for meeting with me yesterday. How are you?
I thought you were publishing the story today.
Oh, we're a long way from that yet.
What do you mean?
We need verification, and some hard evidence.
We don't publish rumors or hear-say.
But I told you how he behaved when I confronted him.
I'm sorry, Tom, but that's not enough.
Please get back to me if you can find someone to corroborate the story.
Or any substantive evidence.
Until then, I'll keep the story warm, and keep our contact confidential.
But the wrong man is going to jail!
I'm sorry. My hands are tied.
a little bit later
hey man I got ur mssgs
Finally!
u crazy?
going to a reporter?
I got to get the truth out.
u think the media cares about truth?
if terrorists attacked the white house while kim k had a live public gyno exam
guess which would be the top story?
I gotta do this.
take my advice
stop digging for dirt
let it go
I can't.
sorry im no help
c u later...
a little bit later
Mr. Bodette, it's Tom Roy.
Yes, Tommy?
Can I ask you something?
Your father told me how worried you were.
You know I was in the passenger seat when we had the accident.
I know.
I can assure you that your father was in the back.
Bill was the driver.
Not your dad. That's why he only suffered a mild concussion.
As you know, I broke my collar bone.
Now, what was it you wanted to ask me?
It's okay. Sorry to bother you.
No bother at all. Be well, Tommy.
a little bit later
Hey, I think I got a lead.
What?
Just spoke with Claude, my dad's campaign manager.
He claims that because my dad got a concussion,
it proves that he was in the back seat.
So?
I learned in Driver's Ed that airbags cause more injuries than we think.
And since the front airbags were both deployed in the car
and since it was a front-end collision
it means that the front passengers got the more serous injuries like a concussion & a broken bone.
Especially since the rear passengers were wearing seat belts.
Your dad got bruises, but my dad got the concussion.
Plus welts from his seat belt.
IDK. It doesn't sound like a smoking gun.
But this is my first real lead.
There's alot more I haven't dug up yet.
Don't you think you're getting a little obsessed?
Nope. My head's clear & focused.
I could use your support, though.
I will give you all of my support & love, but...
But what?
Promise me that if you don't find any real evidence
you will drop it and don't look back.
You have my word. If I reach a dead end, I'll let it go...
just one thing.
Yes?
Promise me you'll be there to dig me out of any hole I dig for myself.
I promise. I won't abandon you. ❤
United we stand. 💕
a little bit later
Hi Lisa. I'm Tom Roy, Hank's son.
How did you get this number?
I saw it on my dad's phone. I need to know what happened that night.
You should not be contacting me. Please leave me alone.
I have a right to know. He's my dad, and I think you can help.
No.
Please. I haven't been able to sleep, or study, and I'm afraid of what I might find.
Then you shouldn't speak with me.
I won't stop searching until I uncover the truth.
I know you can help.
Go away.
No one can make me stop.
Not even my father.
Listen. What you are doing is dangerous.
He can stop you.
He's gotten very powerful.
He can do anything.
You know something about him. What is it?
Nothing.
I saw a message he sent to you that night.
He asked you to meet him for drinks.
What is your relationship to my dad?
I'm just a friend.
We had a drink, he spilled it on himself, and came to my apt to wash it off.
That's all.
I don't think so
This is stupid. You are stupid and shameful.
Stop this or you are going to hurt a lot of people.
Now, Fuck Off!
